This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language models and their ability to track number agreement between subject and verb. Additionally, the use of diagnostic classifiers to understand the representation of linguistic information in neural models is a common topic in this sub-category. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the use of LSTMs (Long Short-Term Memory) in the paper suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper mentions the use of classifiers to improve the performance of language models, which could potentially place it in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as well.
